Members of Maritime Workers Union of Nigeria (MWUN) and Nigerian Association of Road Transport Owners (NARTO) have suspended their plan to embark on an industrial action. The management of Nigerian Ports Authority (NPA) led by its Managing Director, Mohammed Bello Koko facilitated the suspension of the industrial action.   Fresh trouble for Tambuwal, Bala, others as court axes Umahi     2023: Buhari hails APC leaders over choice of candidates     NASU, SSANU reject plan to widen salary disparity inâ€¦   The decision was taken after a meeting between the NPA boss and the leadership of the unions in Lagos. The development is seen by industry watchers as pleasant considering the negative impact the strike would have had in the transport sector. Those at the meeting include Koko, Adenrele Sussana Adesina, Executive Director Finance and Admin, NPA, National President NARTO, Alhaji Yusuf Lawal Othman and Comrade Adewale Adeyanju, President General Maritime Workers Union of Nigeria (MWUN) among others.